In this exercise, we will be writing a JavaScript function to debounce an input handler with a wait time of 300 ms. Debouncing is a technique used to prevent a function from being called multiple times while a user is continuously typing or interacting with an input element. It works by delaying the execution of the function until a certain amount of time has passed since the last call. This is different from throttling, which limits the number of times a function can be called within a given time period.

